Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.36,0:00:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,, historian: n.   历史学家\N They will be able, as it were, to see and hear us in action. But the historian attempting to reconstruct the distant past has always faced with a difficult task.\N他们将能够看到并听到我们的行动。但是，试图重建遥远过去的历史学家一直面临着一项艰巨的任务。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.56,0:00:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,, deduce: v.   推断，推理, scanty: adj. 不足的，贫乏的, clue: n.   线索, insignificant: adj. 不重要的, shed: v.   使流出，泻\N He has to deduce what he can from the few scanty clues available. Even seemingly insignificant remains can shed interesting light on the history of early man.\N他必须从可用的几个少数线索中推断出他能做的一切。即使看似微不足道的遗体也可能对早期人的历史展现出有趣的启示。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.76,0:00:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,, calendar: n.   历法，日历, historian: n.   历史学家, advent: n.   出现，到来，来临, agriculture: n.   农业\N Up to now, historians have assumed that calendars came into being with the advent of agriculture.\N到目前为止，历史学家认为日历是随着农业的出现而开始的。
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.56,0:01:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,, For then man was faced with a real need to understand something about the seasons.\N因为那时，人面临着真正需要了解季节的东西。
